<ContentPage
  title="Open-Source Licenses & Attributions | LazyTools"
  description="LazyTools is built on open-source software. Attributions and licenses for the libraries that power the site and its tools."
  heading="Open-source licenses"
>
  <p>
    LazyTools is built on excellent open-source software. This page lists the projects that power the site and
    its tools, with their licenses. It grows as new tools ship.
  </p>

  <h2>Site framework</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a> — MIT License</li>
    <li><a href="https://preactjs.com">Preact</a> — MIT License</li>
    <li><a href="https://tailwindcss.com">Tailwind CSS</a> — MIT License</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tool engines</h2>
  <p>
    Unit conversion logic is implemented in-house using internationally published unit definitions (BIPM SI
    brochure; NIST Handbook 44; national standards for imperial/US customary units). Future tool categories will
    list their WebAssembly and JavaScript library attributions here (e.g. pdf-lib, ffmpeg.wasm and image codecs,
    with their respective MIT/LGPL licenses and source links).
  </p>
</ContentPage>
